&gt; Oil of oregano is an antibiotic and antifungal. It does not, 
however, kill 
&gt; off the intestinal bacteria that are so important to your 
digestion. It 
&gt; may help in the elimination of the H. Pylorii bacteria (the cause 
of 
&gt; ulcers).
&gt; 
&gt; It&#39;s pretty strong stuff, though, and will burn your mouth if taken 
&gt; directly. Put a couple drops in an ounce or two of another oil 
&gt; (recommended: coconut oil) and drink it that way if you can.
&gt; 
&gt; You can probably get it at a local health food store.
&gt; 
